\chapter{Dataset Description}

The CIFAKE dataset~\cite{bird2024} is a publicly available benchmark
specifically designed for distinguishing real from AI-generated synthetic
images. The dataset consists of a total of 120,000 images split equally
between 60,000 real photographs sourced from the CIFAR-10 dataset and
60,000 AI-generated synthetic images produced using Stable Diffusion v1.4.
All images are in RGB format at a resolution of 32$\times$32 pixels, making
them well-suited for pixel-level analysis. The dataset is partitioned into a
training set of 73,140 images and a test set of 20,000 images, representing a
binary classification task of REAL versus FAKE. The CIFAKE dataset was
published in IEEE Access in 2024 and is freely accessible on Kaggle.

