\chapter{Experimental Results}

All experiments were conducted on an HP Victus laptop equipped with an
NVIDIA GeForce RTX 3050 Laptop GPU (4.3~GB VRAM, CUDA 12.1), running
Windows~11 with PyTorch 2.5.1. The CIFAKE test set of 20,000 images
(10,000 REAL, 10,000 FAKE) was used as the evaluation benchmark.

\section{CNN Training Performance}

The model converges steadily, with training accuracy rising from 88.63\%
at epoch~1 to \textbf{97.93\%} at epoch~10 while the cumulative
Cross-Entropy loss decreases from 304.30 to 59.78. The rapid improvement
between epochs 1 and 2 reflects the model quickly learning dominant visual
features distinguishing CIFAR-10 photographs from Stable
Diffusion-generated images, such as differences in texture regularity,
colour smoothness, and edge sharpness. The final test accuracy is
\textbf{94.53\%}, exceeding the published CIFAKE baseline of
92.98\%~\cite{bird2024} by 1.55 percentage points.

