    \label{fig:test_image2}
\end{figure}

\section{Test Case 2: AI-Generated Animal Image}

The second image was an AI-generated animal figure from an unseen
generator. The CNN correctly classified it as \textbf{FAKE (AI-Generated)}
with 84.9\% confidence. Following FGSM, the mean pixel difference was
\textbf{0.0498} with standard deviation 0.002, exceeding $\tau = 0.0497$
by 0.0001. The detector correctly returned \textbf{ADVERSARIAL DETECTED}.
The heatmap in Figure~\ref{fig:test_image1} shows a concentrated
perturbation cluster localised around the animal body outline, consistent
with steeper loss gradients at the salient foreground subject at lower
