\section{Chrome Extension Prototype}

A Chrome extension was developed to deploy the trained CNN model as a
real-time adversarial image detector in the browser. The extension
consists of two components: a local Flask server running the CNN model at
\texttt{localhost:5000}, and a Chrome MV3 extension that sends image data
from any web page to the server for analysis. Users can right-click any
image on a website and select ``Detect AI / Adversarial Image'' to receive
a popup showing the CNN classification (REAL or FAKE), confidence score,
mean pixel difference, and adversarial detection verdict. The server
processes each request by applying FGSM at $\epsilon = 0.05$ and
comparing the pixel difference against $\tau = 0.0497$.

